description: Self-directed research and learning
globs: research/**
---

Topics the user is learning independently outside coursework: RAG pipelines, ML, and related areas.

Conventions:
- Each subject gets a subfolder (e.g. `RAG-pipelines/`, `ML/`). When a subfolder gets dense, add a `_context_<folder>.md` (copy `templates/_context_TEMPLATE.md`).
- Tag notes with `area/research` plus a subject subtag (e.g. `subject/rag`, `subject/ml`).
- Notes can include paper summaries, implementation notes, experiment logs, or concept breakdowns.
- The user is comfortable with technical depth — don't over-explain fundamentals unless asked.
- Prefer linking to related internship or project notes via [[wikilinks]] when concepts overlap.
